    "content": "<p>A uniform light slender beam AB of section modulus EI is pinned by a frictionless joint A to the ground and supported by a light inextensible cable CB to hang a weight W as shown. If the maximum value of W to avoid buckling of the beam AB is obtained as βπ<sup>2</sup>EI, where&nbsp;π is the ratio of circumference to diameter of a circle, then the value of&nbsp;β is</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzta60qz/fa2b3a6d-72fa-4fbb-a3b1-81b430fb33eb/adc721b0-59eb-11ef-8192-f3618dbf6fb2/file-jaoe38c1lzta60r0.webp?format=webp\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzta60qz/fa2b3a6d-72fa-4fbb-a3b1-81b430fb33eb/adc721b0-59eb-11ef-8192-f3618dbf6fb2/file-jaoe38c1lzta60r0.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2022 Set 1 Strength of Materials - Columns and Struts Question 1 English\">",
