    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lztadv8g/7b59e103-1026-4d0d-8305-adf5f47bdaf0/87fdb600-59ec-11ef-8192-f3618dbf6fb2/file-jaoe38c1lztadv8h.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lztadv8g/7b59e103-1026-4d0d-8305-adf5f47bdaf0/87fdb600-59ec-11ef-8192-f3618dbf6fb2/file-jaoe38c1lztadv8h.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2022 Set 1 Strength of Materials - Columns and Struts Question 1 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>F.B.D. at point B</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lztadrur/a8bfbd0c-ee7e-4c2c-b27d-f1b3c5411cd1/85613930-59ec-11ef-8192-f3618dbf6fb2/file-jaoe38c1lztadrus.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lztadrur/a8bfbd0c-ee7e-4c2c-b27d-f1b3c5411cd1/85613930-59ec-11ef-8192-f3618dbf6fb2/file-jaoe38c1lztadrus.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2022 Set 1 Strength of Materials - Columns and Struts Question 1 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>$\\begin{aligned} &amp; +\\uparrow \\sum F_V=0 \\\\\\\\ &amp; F_{B C} \\sin 30^{\\circ}=\\mathrm{W} \\\\\\\\ &amp; F_{B C}=2 \\mathrm{~W} .........(i) \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\rightarrow+\\sum F_H=0 \\\\\\\\ &amp; F_{A B}=F_{B C} \\cos 30^{\\circ} \\\\\\\\ &amp; F_{A B}=2 W \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\\\\\\\ &amp; F_{A B}=\\sqrt{3} \\mathrm{~W} ........(ii)\\end{aligned}$</p>\n\n<p>The buckling load is given by :</p>\n\n<p>$$ P_C=\\frac{\\pi^2 E I}{L_C^2}=\\frac{\\pi^2 E I}{2.5^2} $$ ..........(iii)</p>\n\n<p>From equation (ii) and (iii)</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\sqrt{3} \\mathrm{~W}=\\frac{\\pi^2 E I}{2.5^2} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\sqrt{3} \\times \\beta \\pi^2 E I=\\frac{\\pi^2 E I}{2.5^2} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\beta=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3} \\times 2.5^2} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\beta=0.092 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
